HEADWORD: Naphthazarin
<hw>Naph*thaz"a*rin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Naphtha</ets>lene + ali<ets>zarin</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A dyestuff, resembling alizarin, obtained from
naphthoquinone as a red crystalline substance with a bright green,
metallic luster; -- called also
<altname>naphthalizarin</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

